I have had two squeeky water pumps on different cars, the first was
fixed by loosening the drive belt.  It was too tight and this put a
strain on the pump bearings.  Check the manufacturers specs first as if
it's too loose it'll come off.
The other was fixed by a bottle of Holts somthing or other, it
lubricated the bearings and had a slightly greasy residue.  It did what
it said on the bottle and quietened down the pump.

